%h1 Lesson 002 [ Install Ubuntu on Laptop ]

%p In the past, during my efforts to install Ubuntu on a laptop, I have put the laptop into a non-bootable state.

%p Obviously this is a bad thing, but it rarely happens.

%p So, before I attempt to install Ubuntu on a laptop, I ensure the laptop is returnable for refund.

%p All laptop vendors have technicians who can quickly transform a non-bootable laptop into a bootable windows-laptop.

%p Many vendors are happy to refund my money if I am dissatisfied with my laptop.
%p If a laptop does not support Ubuntu, I consider that a valid reason for dissatisfaction.

%p Not all vendors honor refund-requests so I pick laptop vendors with care.

%hr/

