%h2 Installation Media (USB-Thumb Drive)

%p Many new laptops have no DVD drive.

%p For those, I use a Ubuntu-USB-Thumb Drive.

%p The easiest way to get a Ubuntu-USB-Thumb Drive is to buy one from Amazon:

%p
  %a(href='https://www.google.com/search?q=amazon+ubuntu+usb+stick' target='x')
    https://www.google.com/search?q=amazon+ubuntu+usb+stick

%p Another way to get a Ubuntu-USB-Thumb Drive, is to create one.

%p To do this you will need access to a laptop or desktop computer which is running Ubuntu.

%p Also you will need a blank 8GB USB-Thumb-Drive:
%p
  %a(href='https://www.google.com/search?q=Amazon+8GB+USB-Thumb-Drive' target='x')
    https://www.google.com/search?q=Amazon+8GB+USB-Thumb-Drive
  
%p Then the general steps are simple:
%ul
  %li Download ISO file from Ubuntu into Downloads folder:
  %li
    %a(href='http://releases.ubuntu.com/16.04.5/ubuntu-16.04.5-desktop-amd64.iso' target='x')
      http://releases.ubuntu.com/16.04.5/ubuntu-16.04.5-desktop-amd64.iso
  %li Start a utility called Startup-Disk-Creator.
  %li Use the wizard inside that utility to create the Ubuntu-USB-Thumb Drive.
  %li If you are like me and get confused by Startup-Disk-Creator, you should turn to Youtube:
  %li
    %a(href='https://www.google.com/search?q=Youtube+Ubuntu+Startup+Disk+Creator' target='x')
      https://www.google.com/search?q=Youtube+Ubuntu+Startup+Disk+Creator
  
